name: Air Fryer Asparagus Tots
author: Soup Loving Nicole
summary: There are broccoli tots and there are cauliflower tots, so why not asparagus tots? These are great on their own but I like to dip them in hollandaise sauce.
ingredients: ¼ cup finely shredded Parmesan cheese
directions: Bring a pot of salted water to a boil over medium-high heat
Drain in a colander and let cool until easily handled, about 5 minutes
Combine asparagus, breadcrumbs, and Parmesan cheese in a large bowl
Knead mixture with your hands until it is the consistency of dough
Form 1 tablespoon of the mixture into a tot
Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Spray the basket of the air fryer with nonstick cooking spray
Place tots in the basket and spray the tops with cooking spray
Fry for 10 minutes, shaking halfway through the cook time
